def: A cutting off; a division; a schism; a faction. South.
A writer of a glossary; a commentator; a scholiast. Hayward.
The quality of being forward; cheerful readiness; promtness;as, the forwardness of Christians in propagating the gospel.

A kind of plain sweet cake seasoned with ginger, and sometimesmade in fanciful shapes. "Gingerbread that was full fine." Chaucer.Gingerbread tree (Bot.), the doom palm; -- so called from theresemblance of its fruit to gingerbread. See Doom Palm.-- Gingerbread work, ornamentation, in architecture or decoration,of a fantastic, trivial, or tawdry character.

The act, process, or result (in the process of parting) ofalloying a button of nearly pure gold with enough silver to reducethe fineness so as to allow acids to attack and remove all metalsexcept the gold; -- called also inquartation. Compare Parting.
Excitomotory; as, excito-motor power or causes.
According to elements; literally; as, the words, "Take, eat;this is my body," elementally understood.
. See Evil eye under Evil, a.
Strong propensity to venery; lust; lecherousness.
